cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.CY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the Lightning Network, a payment channel network built on top of the Bitcoin blockchain. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely as the paper discusses privacy-aware payment channels and proposes a proactive channel rebalancing algorithm. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the Lightning Network is a distributed system. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is relevant as the paper discusses a collaborative approach within the friend of a friend network. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is less likely but still possible as the paper touches on the topic of routing fees and their impact on the network.
